statement.p:
Compute the determinant of
                A=\mat{4 0 0 5;1 7 2 -5;3 0 0 0;8 3 1 7}
                using cofactor expansions. Expand along the rows or columns that require the least amount of work.

answer.p:
The expand along the third row because it only has one nonzero entry.

                    \det(A)=3(-1)^{3+1}.\det \mat{0 0 5;7 2 -5; 3 1 7}
                    \quad =3 \cdot 5(-1)^{1+3}\det \mat{7 2;3 1}
                    \quad = 3(5)(1)(7-6) = 15
                .
                (In the second step, we used the cofactor expansion along the first row since it had only one nonzero entry.)
